      • extractCompositeStringUniquesValueChains

        public static Set<String> extractCompositeStringUniquesValueChains(String theResourceType,
                                                                   List<List<String>> thePartsChoices)
        This method is used to create a set of all possible combinations of parameters across a set of search parameters. An example of why this is needed:

        Let's say we have a unique index on (Patient:gender AND Patient:name). Then we pass in SMITH, John with a gender of male.

        In this case, because the name parameter matches both first and last name, we now need two unique indexes:

        • Patient?gender=male&name=SMITH
        • Patient?gender=male&name=JOHN

        So this recursive algorithm calculates those

        Parameters:
        theResourceType - E.g. Patient
        thePartsChoices - E.g. [[gender=male], [name=SMITH, name=JOHN]]
